<br>
I for one, do not believe that we are inviting guilds too fast.  Nor do i believe that the SGA is &quot;big enough already&quot;.  I have made a few attempts at leading small raids to various locations.  To date it has been difficult to get as many participants as i would like for the raids i have planned.  Recognizing that this is probably in part due to my inexperience with organizing raids, I would nonetheless probably have benefited from having a larger group of members to draw from.  <br>
<br>
I do believe that the SGA is a better organization because there is a stable core membership that communicates effectively across guild boundaries.  I know that the SGA is not a guild, but i still believe that it is a stronger, healthier organization because its members have developed friendships and enjoy spending time together.  I know that in my heart, i feel proud to be a member of the SGA, just as i feel proud to be a member of the Spirit Guardians.  I feel proud of what we have accomplished.  <br>
<br>
This pride and these friendships are important for the success of our raids and for the advancement of our members.  Please ask yourselves how much quicker you respond to calls for help from friend?  Ask yourselves how much closer you pay attention to the well-being of players you know and trust?  <br>
<br>
As Hareq points out, our successes (especially regarding epic quests) have come much more quickly than we originally imagined.  Certainly this success represents one indication of our readiness to move on with the growth of the SGA.  However, at the same time, this success should provide us the motivation to move forward in the right way, so as to guard against the loss of what we have already put together.  <br>
<br>
All things considered, IMHO it probably is the right time for the SGA to move forward.  But let's not put expansion ahead of the well-being of the existing alliance.<br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
Spirit Guardians <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umenniantheelder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mennian The Elder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 2:32:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> Can't say I know much about anything going on here, but I would like to add a couple comments on a very good point Myriah brought up.  In almost joining Familjen and being a member of Heaven and Earth for awhile I can tell everyone, without a doubt, there is always always a shortage of high level clerics and enchanters needed for the completion of epics and large scale raids.  Right now, almost every other day I am asked to help with someones epic (not entirely SGA, mostly friends from previous guilds).  If additional guilds are invited, without fully exploring their class makeup, the strain on the clerics and enchanters currently in SGA might greaten rather than lessen.  <br>
<br>
A couple raids a week is all I really care for, they aren't why I play.  I enjoy grouping with friends and exploring.<br>
With HaE, there were a minimum of three large raids a week, and during the offdays, I was either expected to gain experience so I could better help on future raids, or help people with their epics.  After six weeks, I was exhausted in RL and broke in EQ life from the constant expense of gems that never got reimbursed.<br>
<br>
In addition, epics are great, but seriously, I am not wild about helping every person get an epic, and I think a minimum level, maybe 55, should be set on when someone should be asking others in obtaining their epic.  Obviously some epics, such as the rez stick, are extremely important, and benefit the guild more than just an individual, but in my opinion, every person on the server shouldn't have an epic or it defeats the purpose.  I am definately not saying I won't help a person under level 55 with part of their epic, just saying it would be an exception and I am not going to make a habit of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard>saryrnguildallianceboard</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href=http://www.entercasino.com/main.cgi?refererID=502600>What's your game? Casino On Net</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><IMG SRC="http://service.bfast.com/bfast/serve?bfmid=7279965&siteid=33932331&bfpage=expertc_tax" BORDER="0" WIDTH="1" HEIGHT="1" NOSAVE >
